title._content: Pillars of Hercules in Columbia Gorge

description._content: Description/Notes: "The Pillars of Hercules stand close to the rail-road and always incite the admiration and wonder of those who pass by. On the top of one these basaltic needles grows an ancient fir tree about 40 feet high and which is said to be over one hundred years old."
